SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA REQUIRE THE FUND TO EVALUATE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY THE FUND AND RECOGNIZE A TAX LIABILITY IF THE FUND HAS TAKEN AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES. THE FUND IS SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY TAXING JURISDICTIONS; HOWEVER, THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS FOR ANY TAX PERIODS IN PROGRESS.
ADVERTISEMENTS IN SEVERAL NEWSPAPERS OF GENERAL CIRCULATION AND THE ELECTRONIC VERSIONS OF THOSE NEWSPAPERS AND TELEVISION COMMERCIALS.
THE FUND DOES NOT AWARD SCHOLARSHIPS OR OTHER FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE. THE FUND DOES NOT SOLICIT CONTRIBUTIONS.
